originalText.text: It is rare to find someone who does both massage and acupuncture as well as Jeff. I went to him for both, and was so pleased with his treatment that I continued to have sessions with him. At each session, he listens carefully to my descriptions of what is bothering me, and he always gives due weight to what I say, while also uncovering through his own skill the source of my discomfort. He is skilled at reading pulses, as acupuncturists are trained to do. (Although not all acupuncturists are good at reading pulses, Jeff most certainly is.) He has strong fingers and hands, applying just the right amount of pressure when he massages. I was happy to find a massage therapist who  primarily uses his fingers and hands to massage, rather than relying on the side of his arm for many strokes, as some massage therapists do.  I find that where the massage therapist uses their fingers and hands, as Jeff does, rather than their forearms, the massage is much more effective at relieving any tightness and trigger points. All told, I am very pleased to have found an acupuncturist/massage therapist who is as dedicated as Jeff is to the wellbeing of his patients. Jeff is also an artist as well as an amateur photographer; I enjoy viewing a slide show of his photos while he works on me.

originalText.text:
Jeff’s experience in working with artists in pain is evident in the depth of his wisdom. Not only am I waking up (and going to sleep) with less pain in my joints, my artistic practice and mental health have also taken a much needed positive turn. Being seen and heard by Jeff is helping me rediscover how to move fluidly with myself, how to listen more carefully, and is paramount in keeping myself safe while exploring heavy material at school.
If you are a human - go see Jeff. His warmth and grace alone are worth the visit.

originalText.text: Jeff is an amazing and talented healer.  I limped in to see him, and left walking almost normal - which became 100% normal two days later, after following his instructions for self-care and exercises.   His massage and acupuncture are first rate!

originalText.text: Jeff is a miracle worker and a very special healer. I’m very grateful to know him and to be treated by him. The best acupuncture, pressure point therapy, and massage I’ve received. His expertise is astounding.

originalText.text:
My knee pain was intolerable after complaining to a pair of friends who praised Jeff's skills I booked 2 sessions. He's part Shaman, Confidant, Masseuse and Therapist with an accurate hand for Acupuncture. He thoughtfully explained his course of treatment and after 2 sessions my tendinitis subsided. I gifted a session to a friend and she's hooked. Jeff's an exceptional healer with his 10,000 hours under his belt. His kindness and skills are a refreshing re-set.

Lily
